pkgmetadata.longdescription: # Type stubs for envparseThis package adds type annotations for the [envparse](https://github.com/rconradharris/envparse) library.## Known Issues- The `force` and `preprocessor` parameters have been omitted.- A `default` value of `None` is not allowed for `list()`, `set()`, `tuple()` or `dict()`. Instead, use an empty list/set/tuple/dict as the default.- A schema cannot be provided to `Env.__init__()`, as this would make it impossible to infer the return types of other methods.## Author[Rob Percival](https://www.linkedin.com/in/robpercival/)
